=head1 NAME

rsm.slv.*.avail.pl - scripts to calculate different service status results and save to the database

=head1 SYNOPSIS

rsm.slv.*.avail.pl [--tld <tld>] [--now <timestamp>] [--cycles <cycles>] [--dry-run] [--warnslow <seconds>] [--debug] [--help]

=head1 OPTIONS

=over 8

=item B<--tld> tld

Specify the TLD to process. By default all tlds will be processed.

=item B<--now> timestamp

Specify Unix timestamp within the test cycle to handle. You don't need to specify the first second of the test cycle.

=item B<--cycles> cycles

Specify number cycles to process. By default 1 cycle will be processed.

=item B<--dry-run>

Print data to the screen, do not write anything to the filesystem.

=item B<--warnslow> seconds

Issue a warning in case an SQL query takes more than specified number of seconds. A floating-point number
is supported as seconds (i. e. 0.5, 1, 1.5 are valid).

=item B<--debug>

Run the script in debug mode. This means printing more information.

=item B<--help>

Print a brief help message and exit.

=back

=head1 DESCRIPTION

B<These scripts> are meant to be run by cron but can be run manually in order to cover the data in
time periods when cron was not running.

=head1 EXAMPLES

./rsm.slv.*.avail.pl --from 1420063200 --period 10

=cut
